{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, our analysis of contextrich projects and model improvements suggests that as LLMs get better at contextual processing abilities, the gap between innovation types may further widen rather than narrow-a pattern likely to influence collaboration across knowledge domains and necessitate interventions to balance innovation.",
    "Innovation carries different meanings across disciplines, yet nearly all definitions converge on the creation of new combinations of resources that people perceive as novel and improved (Rogers 2003).",
    "Open-source software development provides an exemplary context for studying innovation because of its transparency, voluntary participation and collaborative development model.",
    "The likelihood of high-quality innovation in open source is enhanced by the skill signaling and reputation building incentives that motivate contributors even when direct financial compensation is absent (Lerner and Tirole, 2002).",
    "This \"private-collective\" innovation model combines individual investment with collective value creation, where participants pursue personal objectives simultaneously while generating shared resources (Hippel and Krogh, 2003)."
  ]
}